    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10145943>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Cataracta microphysa comb. nov. A. Perennial herb with a rhizome of 30–40 cm long. B. One flower per axil, corolla plane rotated with a slight yellowish or greenish tinge. C. The fruiting calyx is teretish, ovate-oblong to campanulate, and open-flaring apically. D. Fruit with a thin, dry pericarp, with dark brown seeds and faveolated-rugous testa. E. The dry fruits dehiscing along irregular lines (Photos of Pilar Zamora-Tavares and Mahinda Martínez)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10145943/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10145945>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Comparisons of habit, flower and fruit traits among Cataracta gen. nov. (A1–A3), Chamesaracha (B1–B3), Oryctes (C1–C3), Physalis (D1–D3), and Quincula (E1–E3) (Photos of Pilar Zamora-Tavares, Mahinda Martínez and Ofelia Vargas-Ponce, B3 provided by Juan Carlos Delgado, C1–C3 by Sophie Winitsky, and E3 by Rocio Deanna)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10145945/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10145947>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Geographic distribution of Cataracta gen. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10145947/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

